  'A seasonal winter day-tour of southwest Jeju (December through February) built around the three things only Jeju does well in winter: snow on Hallasan''s slopes, red camellias in full bloom at Camellia Hill, and pick-your-own Jeju tangerines (gyul) at a working orchard. The route also covers Cheonjeyeon Falls, Jusangjeolli columnar cliffs, and the Osulloc Tea Museum. Hotel pickup in Jeju City, English/Chinese-speaking licensed guide.',
